This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for language identification, which are typically covered under the arXiv category of Computer Science - Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of hierarchical models and contextualized word-level representations also suggests a focus on deep learning and neural networks, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the ability to detect code-switching, which involves analyzing language use in multilingual contexts, and could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
